## Key rules for agents

- **TDD** — write failing tests before any implementation. Use `/plan <task>` to generate acceptance tests first.
- **Linear** — before starting non-trivial work, create or reference a Linear issue. Use `/start-task` if one does not exist.
{{#if lint_command}}- **Lint** — `{{lint_command}}` must pass before closing a task. The `pre-commit-gate` hook enforces this on every commit.
{{/if}}
- **No secrets in code** — never hardcode API keys, tokens, passwords, or personal data (SSN, card numbers). Use `os.environ['KEY']` or a `.env` file (gitignored). The `secret-guard` hook will block any write that contains a real secret.
{{#if linear_issue_prefix}}
## Linear ↔ GitHub

| Thing | Format | Effect |
|---|---|---|
| Branch | `<username>/{{linear_issue_prefix}}-<N>-<slug>` — **copy from Linear** | Copying triggers "Started" status + self-assign |
| Commit | `{{linear_issue_prefix}}-N: <what and why>` | Linear links the commit to the issue |
| PR title + body | `{{linear_issue_prefix}}-N: <title>` + `Fixes {{linear_issue_prefix}}-N` in body | Moves issue to Done on merge |

**Always get the branch name from Linear's "Copy git branch" button.** That action fires the "move to Started" and "assign to self" automations. Manually typed branch names do not trigger them. For agents: if no branch name is supplied, construct it as `<linear-username>/{{linear_issue_prefix}}-<N>-<title-slug>` (lowercase, hyphens only).
{{/if}}
